,"reasoning_summary": "Stereotype threat occurs when individuals are aware of negative stereotypes associated with their group membership and worry about confirming those stereotypes. In STEM fields, underrepresented groups may experience higher levels of stereotype threat due to the perceived lack of fit between their gender or racial identity and the dominant cultural norms in these fields. This can lead to a self-fulfilling prophecy, where individuals from underrepresented groups are less likely to pursue STEM careers or perform well in these fields due to the fear of confirming negative stereotypes. Addressing stereotype threat is crucial for promoting diversity and inclusion in STEM fields, as it can help to reduce the achievement gap between underrepresented groups and their peers from dominant groups. By creating a more inclusive and supportive learning environment, we can encourage individuals from all backgrounds to pursue STEM careers and reach their full potential."
